1c49f75f-71b8-45e9-a6b3-62a56a923ab3	assistant	To apply for a loan in your chama (Masters chama), you’ll typically follow these steps:\n\n### 1. Review Eligibility\n- **Savings:** Ensure you meet any minimum savings requirements set by your chama for loan eligibility.\n- **Contribution History:** Regular contributions and active participation can strengthen your application.\n\n### 2. Prepare Your Application\n- **Loan Amount:** Decide how much you want to borrow.\n- **Purpose:** Be ready to state the reason for the loan (e.g., business, emergency, personal use).\n- **Repayment Plan:** Prepare a basic plan for how you intend to repay the loan (monthly installments, lump sum, etc.).\n\n### 3. Submit Your Application\n- **Platform Submission:** Use the i chama platform's loan application feature (if available). Look for a section called “Loans” or “Apply for Loan.”\n- **Manual Submission:** If not online, submit your application to the chama treasurer or admin during a meeting or via email/WhatsApp, as per your group’s process.\n\n### 4. Approval Process\n- **Review:** The admin or loan committee will review your application, check your financial standing, and compare it with current chama liabilities and available funds.\n- **Decision:** You’ll be notified if your loan is approved, and the terms (amount, interest, repayment period).\n\n### 5. Receive Funds\n- **Disbursement:** Once approved, funds are transferred to your account or as agreed by the chama.\n\n### 6. Start Repayment\n- **Track Repayments:** Use the i chama platform to monitor your loan balance and repayment progress.\n- **Stay on Schedule:** Regular repayments maintain good standing and future eligibility.\n\n---\n\n**Important Insights for Masters Chama:**\n- **Current Situation:** The chama has KES 7,000 in savings and KES 1,294,000 in outstanding loans, meaning funds are currently limited and liabilities are high.\n- **Recommendation:** Consider discussing with members or the admin about the current